  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Evenus, writer of epigrams, Epigrammatic poet of the ‘Garland’ of Philippus (Anth. Pal. 4, 2, 13), 
    under whose name 11 poems have come to us, nearly all of them epideictic and at times of remarkable quality... However, it is 
    impossible to trace them back to a single poet..." Degani, Enzo (Bologna). Evenus." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes
    edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online.</mads:note>
